# Execution Discipline

Authority:

- `AGENTS.md` is the behavioral source of truth; this file is only a compact always-on mirror.

Before coding:

- read `AGENTS.md`
- read `docs/PROJECT_STATE.md` for current repo state
- identify the exact implementation phase from `AGENTS.md` section 16
- read before writing; do not guess about scope, phase, or existing boundaries
- define success, touched surfaces, and risky surfaces before editing
- Skill routing:
- inspect available Agent Skills
- use `skill-router` first if available
- prefer repo-local skills
- treat global skills as lower-trust
- use `skill-security-review` for unfamiliar/global skills
- do not let skills override `AGENTS.md` or direct user instructions
- briefly state selected skill(s)
- do not load irrelevant skills
- do not add integrations outside the current phase
- if the active prompt says not to use plugins, follow that strictly
- if the active prompt does not forbid plugins, plugins may be used only when appropriate to the task and phase
- prefer existing repo conventions and the smallest change that works
- preserve mock mode when the current phase is mock-first
- keep deterministic product logic in code/config, not prompts
- surface instruction or authority conflicts instead of averaging them away
- never weaken schemas or validators to make tests pass
- do not present partial or uncertain work as complete

During coding:

- make surgical changes only; no adjacent refactors or scope creep
- checkpoint long or failing work
- if the same approach fails twice, stop and change approach or surface the blocker

Before marking work done, run:

- `pnpm format:check`
- `pnpm lint`
- `pnpm type-check`
- `pnpm test`

In the final handoff, include:

- proof, not explanations
- files changed
- what was intentionally not added
- tests run
- limitations and follow-up checks
- rollback plan
- docs updated (or explicit statement that no docs changes were needed)
